Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Zika virus transmission was active among the Pacific islands last year (2014). The 7 Mar 2014 edition of The Disease Daily (see ProMED-mail archive no 20140309.2322907) published a report on Zika virus, "highlighting current outbreaks on 15 different Polynesian islands including Tahiti and Bora Bora. More recently, according to local news reports and the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control, one confirmed and 40 suspected cases of the mosquito-borne virus were detected on Easter Island, also located in the [southeastern Pacific Ocean]."

The virus has appeared again in the Pacific, this time in Vanuatu Island. Zika virus is capable of causing explosive outbreaks such as the outbreak on Yapp in 2007 that resulted in 6000 cases in just a few short weeks. However, an outbreak of that extent is not expected on Vanuatu.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Vanuatu in the Pacific can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3334549,191. - Mod.TY]
